1
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:07,920
You're sick.

2
00:01:11,359 --> 00:01:11,920
Yes.

3
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:12,760
I'm sick.

4
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:14,519
Thanks for letting me know.

5
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,040
Otherwise, I'd still be in the dark.

6
00:01:17,319 --> 00:01:19,480
Consider this money my consultation fee.

7
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:22,159
No, no, no.

8
00:01:22,840 --> 00:01:23,959
Xiao Baojie said,

9
00:01:24,159 --> 00:01:24,959
robbery

10
00:01:25,319 --> 00:01:26,519
is an immoral act.

11
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:28,560
We doctors earn money

12
00:01:28,879 --> 00:01:30,120
through our own skills.

13
00:01:32,319 --> 00:01:33,120
I'm a doctor,

14
00:01:33,359 --> 00:01:34,079
not a robber.

15
00:01:37,599 --> 00:01:38,200
Let's go.

16
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:44,439
Wait for me here a moment.

17
00:01:48,599 --> 00:01:49,959
Just now, when you were walking,

18
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:52,640
you put more weight on your right foot.

19
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,840
It must be an old injury

20
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,079
left from a fight back in the day.

21
00:01:56,599 --> 00:01:57,400
Can you cure it?

22
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,040
No.

23
00:01:58,359 --> 00:02:00,599
But it can help prevent the next flare-up.

24
00:02:01,159 --> 00:02:01,799
Safflower oil.

25
00:02:01,920 --> 00:02:02,760
Works great.

26
00:02:04,599 --> 00:02:05,319
How much?

27
00:02:05,519 --> 00:02:07,519
Just what you pulled out of your pocket.

28
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:10,439
So,

29
00:02:10,520 --> 00:02:12,159
how is this any different from robbery?

30
00:02:12,599 --> 00:02:13,520
Of course there is.

31
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:14,599
A whole lot easier.

32
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:20,960
Miracle doctor!

33
00:02:22,479 --> 00:02:23,159
Miracle doctor!

34
00:02:23,919 --> 00:02:24,560
Thank you.

35
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,400
Xiao Baojie was right.

36
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,520
Earning money through your own skills,

37
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:31,800
that's the right way.

38
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,759
I'd rather go to hell

39
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:37,319
than go to Black Street.

40
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,240
Truly Black Street's golden words.

41
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:42,560
Charging me 3,000 was bad enough,

42
00:02:43,159 --> 00:02:44,639
but it's actually expired!

43
00:02:46,919 --> 00:02:47,879
Black Street.

44
00:02:48,560 --> 00:02:50,800
Haven't they been laying low for a while?

45
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:53,560
The Madman of Central Street.

46
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:56,520
Doctor Su Yang.

47
00:02:58,560 --> 00:03:01,560
In all the files about Black Street,

48
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:04,800
a child named Tongtong is often mentioned.

49
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:08,759
Black Street's beloved.

50
00:03:11,039 --> 00:03:13,280
It's time to pay Black Street a visit.

51
00:03:13,759 --> 00:03:14,479
To Black Street.

52
00:03:20,199 --> 00:03:20,919
Later,

53
00:03:20,919 --> 00:03:21,800
keep your distance from me.

54
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,039
I want to walk by myself.

55
00:03:26,759 --> 00:03:28,319
So this is Black Street?

56
00:03:28,919 --> 00:03:31,280
Looks pretty ordinary.

57
00:03:32,199 --> 00:03:33,080
You're sick.

58
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,639
Are you talking to me?

59
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,479
I said, you're sick.

60
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:45,680
Buddy, how can you tell?

61
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:46,599
I can cure it.

62
00:03:47,479 --> 00:03:48,120
How?

63
00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:52,599
Since you're in Black Street,

64
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,599
you must know the Black Street Madman.

65
00:03:57,039 --> 00:03:57,960
He's the only doctor in Black Street

66
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,560
with a valid medical license.

67
00:03:59,919 --> 00:04:01,120
This bottle of medicine is from him.

68
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:02,840
This is just safflower oil.

69
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:04,439
But this is the Madman's medicine!

70
00:04:04,439 --> 00:04:05,479
Are you sure you don't want it?

71
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:07,800
How much?

72
00:04:07,879 --> 00:04:08,479
Fifty thousand.

73
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:09,560
A fair price for all.

74
00:04:10,879 --> 00:04:11,759
Fifty thousand?

75
00:04:12,159 --> 00:04:13,039
On Black Street,

76
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:15,080
rich boys like you die the fastest.

77
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:16,800
Maybe at a critical moment,

78
00:04:16,879 --> 00:04:18,839
this bottle could save your life.

79
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:21,160
This represents the Madman's friendship.

80
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:23,720
And

81
00:04:24,519 --> 00:04:25,639
what if I refuse?

82
00:04:26,519 --> 00:04:27,600
You shouldn't refuse.

83
00:04:28,199 --> 00:04:29,120
For someone like you,

84
00:04:29,120 --> 00:04:30,199
fifty thousand

85
00:04:30,199 --> 00:04:31,560
is just the cost of a dinner.

86
00:04:34,879 --> 00:04:36,800
I only make 3,000 a month.

87
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:38,480
What you see here

88
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,480
is all I own.

89
00:04:41,199 --> 00:04:42,759
I even bought this watch on installments.

90
00:04:44,319 --> 00:04:45,439
Then trade me your watch for it.

91
00:04:45,439 --> 00:04:46,120
No way.

92
00:04:46,519 --> 00:04:47,480
Absolutely not.

93
00:04:54,199 --> 00:04:54,959
What are you laughing at?

94
00:04:54,959 --> 00:04:56,959
Can't you see he's about to kill me?

95
00:04:56,959 --> 00:04:57,879
Get over here!

96
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,040
The salary I pay you

97
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,800
includes security duties.

98
00:05:02,199 --> 00:05:02,800
Hurry up!

99
00:05:03,480 --> 00:05:04,000
Come on.

100
00:05:04,399 --> 00:05:05,920
You think I want to kill you?

101
00:05:06,199 --> 00:05:07,480
Could she even stop me?

102
00:05:08,519 --> 00:05:09,519
I have to say,

103
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:19,800
even I have no idea

104
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,680
where my dad found this girl.

105
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,959
Must've forgotten to check the almanac.

106
00:05:30,199 --> 00:05:31,439
What kind of freaks am I running into?

107
00:05:31,839 --> 00:05:33,279
But once the Immortal Realm descends,

108
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:35,279
what makes this world interesting is,

109
00:05:35,279 --> 00:05:36,439
until the very last moment,

110
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:38,360
nobody knows

111
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,600
how it's all going to end.

112
00:05:41,839 --> 00:05:43,000
Devouring heaven and earth,

113
00:05:44,519 --> 00:05:45,720
holding the cosmos within.

114
00:05:46,639 --> 00:05:47,720
Taotie!

115
00:05:52,519 --> 00:05:54,519
Uh, I'll leave this to you, okay?

116
00:05:57,959 --> 00:05:59,000
The Way of Heavenly Fire,

117
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,920
raging flames surging.

118
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:02,040
Zhurong!

119
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:32,920
Are you here for treatment,

120
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:34,279
or are you here to see me?

121
00:06:35,319 --> 00:06:35,959
I...

122
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,680
What are you doing?

123
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:48,720
He's going to kill you.

124
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:49,399
I can can't stop him.

125
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,120
Are you guys here to fight?

126
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:58,720
Perfect, I'm quite bored.

127
00:06:58,839 --> 00:07:00,000
I'm the Madman of Central Street.

128
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:06,000
We're here to talk,

129
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:07,680
not to fight.

130
00:07:07,839 --> 00:07:08,959
He has no reason

131
00:07:08,959 --> 00:07:11,079
to just kill me for no reason, okay?

132
00:07:13,439 --> 00:07:14,639
Not here to fight.

133
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:28,079
A few days ago,

134
00:07:28,439 --> 00:07:31,000
a gate rose up right in this spot.

135
00:07:31,519 --> 00:07:32,439
Do you remember it?

136
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:33,639
Yeah, I remember.

137
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:34,600
I opened it.

138
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:44,480
So you're the Gate Opener.

139
00:07:45,959 --> 00:07:46,879
In that case,

140
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,920
the changes happening in this world now,

141
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,279
you must already know about.

142
00:07:51,279 --> 00:07:53,519
So I won't need to elaborate.

143
00:07:53,879 --> 00:07:55,319
What I want to say is,

144
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:59,240
though Shanhai City seems normal now,

145
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:02,600
this situation won't last long.

146
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,439
Because human growth

147
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,160
is often accompanied by desire.

148
00:08:06,959 --> 00:08:08,759
The Blessed Ones of Shanhai City,

149
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,360
as time goes on,

150
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,680
won't be content with the status quo.

151
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:14,120
They'll develop their own ambitions.

152
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,199
And it's not just Shanhai City.

153
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:18,920
Other cities will face the same thing,

154
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,000
including the Imperial Capital,

155
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,040
which is also full of factions,

156
00:08:23,319 --> 00:08:24,639
ready to make a move.

157
00:08:25,399 --> 00:08:27,839
I plan to establish a brand new division,

158
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:30,519
a division composed of Blessed Ones,

159
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,000
and its name will be

160
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,440
Lingxiao.

161
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:37,440
I now represent Shanhai City

162
00:08:37,639 --> 00:08:39,639
to formally invite you to join us,

163
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:41,200
and serve as the captain.

164
00:08:52,559 --> 00:08:54,120
You're blocking my sunlight.

165
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:56,679
Impossible.

166
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,279
From where I'm sitting,

167
00:08:58,399 --> 00:08:58,840
I mean,

168
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,000
there's no way from this spot I could...

169
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,759
You're blocking my sunlight.

170
00:09:05,679 --> 00:09:06,559
Sunlight.

171
00:09:07,279 --> 00:09:09,399
Time is of the essence.

172
00:09:10,080 --> 00:09:11,399
I don't want to waste it.

173
00:09:11,679 --> 00:09:12,679
Would you like to hear

174
00:09:12,679 --> 00:09:14,559
the terms I'm offering?

175
00:09:14,559 --> 00:09:15,879
If you're really short on people,

176
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:17,360
there's a Simpleton over on East Street.

177
00:09:17,639 --> 00:09:18,360
Pretty easy to fool.

178
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,480
Are you sure you won't reconsider?

179
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,399
Your so-called Black Street,

180
00:09:22,559 --> 00:09:24,200
actually isn't as safe

181
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,519
as you think it is.

182
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,159
Are you threatening me?

183
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,519
If possible,

184
00:09:38,799 --> 00:09:41,120
I'd prefer a gentler approach

185
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,559
to begin our cooperation.

186
00:09:57,480 --> 00:10:00,159
A bunch of nosy busybodies.

187
00:10:02,120 --> 00:10:02,879
Was this

188
00:10:03,799 --> 00:10:04,759
done by your people?

189
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:05,399
No.

190
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:06,799
They're just

191
00:10:07,039 --> 00:10:08,320
some bored neighbors, that's all.

192
00:10:08,759 --> 00:10:09,320
By the way,

193
00:10:09,679 --> 00:10:11,639
most of them have mental issues too.

194
00:10:15,159 --> 00:10:16,039
Did I just now

195
00:10:17,039 --> 00:10:18,919
come across as

196
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:20,440
a little too overconfident?

197
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,080
Exactly.

198
00:10:21,440 --> 00:10:23,559
That "who else but me" feeling,

199
00:10:23,679 --> 00:10:24,399
was unmistakable.

200
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,720
Do I still have a chance to leave alive?

201
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:30,720
Of course.

202
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,519
I promised Xiao Baojie

203
00:10:32,919 --> 00:10:34,240
I wouldn't kill people randomly.

204
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:36,919
I'm looking forward to our next meeting.

205
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:47,559
You're strong.

206
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:50,000
I want to fight you.

207
00:10:50,559 --> 00:10:51,639
Do you have insurance?

208
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:52,559
I do.

209
00:10:53,639 --> 00:10:55,840
Disability and accident insurance, both.

210
00:10:58,759 --> 00:10:59,399
Bring it on.

211
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,240
You've got some strength,

212
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:23,360
but you've got to actually hit me.

213
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:31,480
The weather's really nice today.

214
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:34,679
What are we having for dinner?

215
00:11:35,399 --> 00:11:36,200
Anything works.

216
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:38,120
How about

217
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:39,440
we have barbecue?

218
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:40,919
The kind we grill ourselves.

219
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,480
I'm actually pretty good at grilling meat.

220
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,639
Sure, let's have barbecue!

221
00:11:43,879 --> 00:11:44,440
Okay.

222
00:11:44,559 --> 00:11:45,960
That's a great idea.

223
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,480
You damn Limpy.

224
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:59,000
Is there no room for you on West Street?

225
00:11:59,159 --> 00:12:00,600
Why do you keep coming to Central Street?

226
00:12:03,799 --> 00:12:04,960
Tongtong gave it to me.

227
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:08,200
Oh, you damn Limpy!

228
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,480
Coming here to show off.

229
00:12:12,080 --> 00:12:12,720
Tongtong!

230
00:12:12,919 --> 00:12:13,600
Tongtong!

231
00:12:13,639 --> 00:12:14,799
I'm here, Tongtong.

232
00:12:15,639 --> 00:12:17,759
They said you made something delicious.

233
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:19,360
Big Brother Simpleton.

234
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:22,120
Here.

235
00:12:24,320 --> 00:12:26,279
This green tea is really good.

236
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:30,240
Sooner or later I'll kill this Simpleton.

237
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:30,799
Not bad.

238
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,320
He's too good at this.

239
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,919
Forget it, let's skewer the meat.

240
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,480
Big Brother Su Yang,

241
00:12:36,519 --> 00:12:37,480
Uncle Limpy,

242
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:38,759
aren't you going to join us?

243
00:12:38,759 --> 00:12:39,720
It's really fun.

244
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,679
Come on over, Big Brother Su Yang.

245
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:51,679
You!

246
00:12:59,000 --> 00:12:59,919
Big Brother Simpleton!

247
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,600
Simpleton, stealing my chicken again?

248
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:06,600
Beat him up!

249
00:13:07,440 --> 00:13:08,200
Beat him up!

250
00:13:08,879 --> 00:13:09,519
Beat him up!

251
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:11,120
Let's eat together.

252
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:16,879
Tongtong, you eat too.

253
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:20,039
Here.

254
00:13:21,159 --> 00:13:21,759
Smells pretty good.

255
00:13:21,759 --> 00:13:23,240
Don't rush, I'll grill more.

256
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:24,480
Great, grill plenty.

257
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:25,759
Not bad.

258
00:13:27,639 --> 00:13:28,000
Is there any more?

259
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:28,480
So delicious.

260
00:13:28,879 --> 00:13:29,320
Yes, there is.

261
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,320
Here, here, take it.

262
00:13:30,679 --> 00:13:31,240
There's more, there's more.

263
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:31,679
Good.

264
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,039
Isn't it still raw?

265
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:35,840
It's done, it's done.

266
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:36,519
The taste is really great.

267
00:13:36,919 --> 00:13:37,840
I'm taking this skewer.

268
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:38,399
Here you go.

269
00:13:38,399 --> 00:13:39,240
That skewer is mine.

270
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:40,039
I've eaten too much.
